references: We evaluate the time overhead of the proposed client selection strategy, and the results are presented in Table I. The time overhead analysis is conducted on the FMNIST dataset under the 1SPC scenario, with similar observations across other scenarios. In Table I, the first row focuses on the time solely for client selection within a communication round, while the second row denotes the overall time required for a complete communication round, including client selection, local updates, and global aggregation.
